BCCDI Prompt
============

The BCCDI prompt indicates whether the 68332 is running ('#' prompt) or
stopped ('%' prompt).  Most commands affecting the MCU, such as
read/write memory, register, etc, can only execute when the MCU is stopped.
An error message is displayed if the MCU is running.

BCCDI Command List
==================

ABORT
stop target MCU

	This command halts the 68332 by asserting BKPT on the background mode
	interface.

BR <n> <addr> <mask>

	This command sets an address and mask value into the comparitor
	register given by <n>.  n may be 0 to 3.  The MSB of the address and
	mask are composed of several control signals as listed below:

Bit     31      30      29      28      27      26      25      24
Signal  DS      AS      SIZ1    SIZ0    R/W     FC2     FC1     FC0

	The lower three bytes contain the 24 bit breakpoint address.

CALL <addr>
call user code patch

	This function calls a user subroutine, stopping the 68332 when an RTS
	is executed.

ECHO [X]
turn off/toggle character echo

	ECHO toggles the character echo on the DI serial port.  ECHO X turns
	off the echo unconditionally.

GO [<addr>]
start execution at PC or specified address

	GO restarts the aborted MCU.  If an address is specified on the
	command line, execution resumes from that address, otherwise the
	contents of the program counter are used as the start of execution.

HELP

