NMI
assert level 7 interrupt on 332

	I haven't tried this one but I assume it works.

NOBR <n>
disable breakpoint register n

	This (I assume) turns off the breakpoint in the register indicated by
	n.

MR <size> <address>
memory read

	This performs a read from memory at the address specified.  The size
	must also be specified;  either B,W, or L is legal.  The result will
	be printed in hex.

MW <size> <address> <data>
memory write

	A memory write is performed at the specified address, with the given
	size.

PROG

	At the moment I have no idea how this command works.

RC <addr>
read comparitor

	The specified address in the breakpoint gate array is read and
	returned as a 32 bit number.  The address may range from 0 to 3F.

RD <regname>
read CPU register

WR <regname> <value>
write CPU register

        The contents of the specified CPU register are displayed (written).
        The name used to specify a register is given below:

	A0 through A6, D0 through D7            use name as is
	PC (program counter)                    S0
	VBR (vector base register)              SA
	SR (status register)                    SB
	USP (user stack pointer)                SC
	SSP (system stack pointer)              SD
	SFC (source function code reg.)         SE
	DFC (destination function code reg.)    SF

RESET <type>

	The 68332 is reset.  Either a full hardware reset is performed (type
	= 'H'), or just a software reset (type = 'S').

STAT

	This command will display the status of the Freeze, Halt, and Reset
	inputs into the 68332.
